A little bit of butter.

33:47.110 --> 33:50.180
And milk.

33:50.220 --> 33:54.360
- Mmm.
- Now this is a yak, no, leg.

33:54.390 --> 33:56.220
Yak leg.

33:56.260 --> 33:56.760
♪

34:00.500 --> 34:01.913
So does meat eating
go all the way back

34:01.920 --> 34:04.400
or were people vegetarian...
All the way back.

34:04.440 --> 34:05.710
All the way.
In fact,

34:05.750 --> 34:08.550
the Bhutanese were
considered cannibals.

34:08.580 --> 34:10.239
Say that again.

34:10.270 --> 34:12.380
Bhutanese were
considered cannibals.

34:12.409 --> 34:16.100
The only vegetable we had
was potato and radish.

34:16.139 --> 34:17.550
That's it, nothing else.
Wow.

34:17.590 --> 34:20.590
People don't kill,
but they would eat,

34:20.630 --> 34:23.389
you know, one another
if somebody dies.

34:23.420 --> 34:24.763
We are not supposed
to eat each other.

34:24.770 --> 34:26.219
You're not supposed to eat yak.

34:26.250 --> 34:27.592
No, no, we are not supposed
to eat meat.

34:27.600 --> 34:29.260
You're not supposed
to eat meats.

34:29.290 --> 34:30.873
Buddhism, I mean,
the hard-core Buddhism.

34:30.880 --> 34:32.670
But culturally,
because of terrain,

34:32.710 --> 34:35.120
we had no choice.
Right.

34:35.159 --> 34:36.920
Ooh, is that bete nut?

34:36.949 --> 34:38.260
- Yeah.
- Betel nut.

34:38.300 --> 34:40.440
- Oh, can I try?
- Yeah. Yeah.

34:40.469 --> 34:42.170
I'm not having it.

34:42.199 --> 34:44.170
- Have you done it?
- Yes, yes, I have.

34:45.340 --> 34:48.340
You asked for it.
And you chew up the green?

34:48.380 --> 34:49.929
Yeah, everything
chewed together...

34:49.969 --> 34:52.350
Like cud.

34:55.830 --> 34:57.630
Whoa. Oh man.

34:57.660 --> 35:00.250
Getting a buzz?

35:00.290 --> 35:03.530
My whole mouth is numb.

35:03.570 --> 35:06.290
I got to do something
about this.

35:10.540 --> 35:12.200
Totally high off of that thing.

35:16.820 --> 35:20.510
♪

35:20.550 --> 35:23.650
Ah, jeez, just stepped
into a fresh loaf of shit.

35:23.690 --> 35:24.720
Ugh.

35:30.390 --> 35:32.280
♪

35:32.320 --> 35:34.320
Whee!

35:34.360 --> 35:35.840
Ah, right here. Ah, yeah.

35:35.870 --> 35:40.190
Whoa, jeez.
It's a serious distance.

35:40.220 --> 35:41.530
The rules are simple.

35:41.570 --> 35:44.500
Shoot your arrow the length
of 1 1/2 football fields

35:44.540 --> 35:46.850
high in the air,
in this case across

35:46.880 --> 35:49.540
the East-West Highway,
all the way, hopefully,

35:49.580 --> 35:50.920
into a small target.

35:50.960 --> 35:52.750
Good luck with that.
That's like...

35:52.790 --> 35:55.240
You would need a .50 caliber
to hit that target.

35:55.270 --> 35:57.830
I could barely see it
flying through the air.

35:57.860 --> 36:00.350
Can you see the arrows?
No.

36:00.380 --> 36:02.210
Yeah!

36:14.400 --> 36:15.780
Wow, close.

36:15.810 --> 36:17.780
What's interesting
is the other team

36:17.810 --> 36:19.950
is often standing by the target,

36:19.990 --> 36:22.020
and hanging out looking cool
for as long as possible

36:22.060 --> 36:25.230
as an arrow flies
in your general direction

36:25.270 --> 36:26.610
is standard practice.

36:26.650 --> 36:28.340
Yeah, yeah!

36:28.370 --> 36:30.930
Whoo!

36:34.280 --> 36:37.690
When points are scored,
there's singing and dancing

36:37.730 --> 36:39.630
and a fair amount of
what can only be called

36:39.660 --> 36:40.730
playful taunting.

36:40.770 --> 36:42.390
- Yeah!
- Whoo!

36:43.600 --> 36:46.600
The Bhutanese version
of "In your face!"

36:48.390 --> 36:50.050
Brag dance.

36:52.570 --> 36:54.540
- They're drinking that.
- Yeah.

36:54.570 --> 36:56.610
What could possibly go wrong?

37:05.450 --> 37:06.790
One-in-a-million shot.

37:06.830 --> 37:08.380
Doonk!

37:08.410 --> 37:10.550
I love the little kid over
there with the juice box,

37:10.590 --> 37:13.320
ten feet from the line of fire.

37:13.350 --> 37:14.490
Ah!

37:17.390 --> 37:18.420
Whoa, hey.

37:18.460 --> 37:19.630
Whoa!

37:24.950 --> 37:26.950
What are they screaming?

37:27.780 --> 37:29.300
Why?

37:30.440 --> 37:31.843
- So they're anti-cheerleaders.
- Yes.

37:31.850 --> 37:33.370
What are they saying, though?

37:33.410 --> 37:35.860
Oh, the short guy,
he can't hit, so...

37:35.890 --> 37:37.620
They calling him short?

37:37.650 --> 37:40.450
Yeah. All the bald head
and everything.

37:43.550 --> 37:45.380
♪

37:47.660 --> 37:50.490
♪

37:50.530 --> 37:52.490
Whoa!

37:55.430 --> 37:56.950
Whoa.

38:00.400 --> 38:03.710
♪

38:07.090 --> 38:08.960
♪

38:15.480 --> 38:19.070
♪

38:45.620 --> 38:47.890
♪

38:47.930 --> 38:50.030
This is very religious site.

38:50.070 --> 38:52.170
It's called the Burning Lake.

38:52.210 --> 38:54.420
Burning Lake or Burning River?

38:54.450 --> 38:56.900
The Burning Lake, but I
think it's actually a river.

38:59.040 --> 39:01.010
I see people are leaving
prayer flags

39:01.040 --> 39:02.430
and these things.

39:02.460 --> 39:05.080
These are called sasas,
these offerings.

39:05.120 --> 39:06.500
Sometimes they're made
out of clay,

39:06.530 --> 39:07.950
and sometimes
they're made out of

39:07.980 --> 39:09.740
actually the ashes of the dead.

39:09.780 --> 39:11.540
Whoa.

39:13.440 --> 39:14.890
Wow, that's pretty awesome.

39:14.920 --> 39:16.990
It's beautiful.

39:18.650 --> 39:20.510
A little pile of incense.

39:29.140 --> 39:31.450
♪

39:31.490 --> 39:33.590
Where do you think
this country is headed?

39:33.630 --> 39:35.730
Honestly, I don't know
what I believe.

39:35.770 --> 39:38.050
I don't know... I don't know
if it's good or bad.

39:38.080 --> 39:40.220
It seems like Shangri-La.

39:40.260 --> 39:41.423
Like, for the place
that invented

39:41.430 --> 39:43.430
Gross National Happiness,
they're content

39:43.470 --> 39:45.610
at under $2 a day.
Yes.

39:45.640 --> 39:47.440
I don't want my child
herding yak,

39:47.470 --> 39:50.780
and I don't know that a lot
of parents do, even here.

39:50.820 --> 39:52.440
Having a fully paved road across

39:52.480 --> 39:54.240
this entire country,
this country's gonna be

39:54.270 --> 39:55.643
a very, very different place
in five years.

39:55.650 --> 39:59.140
The question is, do they stay
committed to happiness

39:59.170 --> 40:01.170
and not to consumption?
Ooh.

40:01.210 --> 40:03.140
Getting off the plane
when we got here,

40:03.180 --> 40:05.140
there were many flat-screen TVs.

40:05.180 --> 40:07.560
First comes electricity,
then comes the television,

40:07.590 --> 40:10.840
then come pop stars
and materialism.

40:10.870 --> 40:12.600
But maybe that's arrogant.
Maybe that's just,

40:12.630 --> 40:15.530
you know, easy for me to say.
I don't know.

40:15.570 --> 40:16.950
A lot of the people
we talked to,

40:16.980 --> 40:18.873
there's a tremendous amount
of respect of what they have.

40:18.880 --> 40:21.780
We're finally seeing
the effects of climate change

40:21.810 --> 40:23.610
in a terrifying way,

40:23.640 --> 40:25.013
which they're all
gonna be able to witness

40:25.020 --> 40:26.610
on their flat-screen TVs.

40:26.650 --> 40:28.860
You know, I think people
are gonna really hold on

40:28.890 --> 40:30.170
to treasures like this.

40:30.200 --> 40:31.790
I know it's beautiful.

40:31.820 --> 40:34.660
I'm glad it hasn't been
[...] up yet by the world.

40:34.690 --> 40:35.190
♪

